WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:12.680
Look. I wish I could help you.
but that money was seized

2
00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:14.414
as part of an investigation

3
00:00:14.516 --> 00:00:17.919
into the illegal poker game
at your residence.

4
00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:21.188
-So you can just keep it?
-It's called civil forfeiture.

5
00:00:21.288 --> 00:00:23.190
And there's no way
we can get it back?

6
00:00:23.290 --> 00:00:26.594
I mean. there's a slim chance.
but it's a lengthy process.

7
00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:29.263
Hey. Chief. where do you want
this new espresso machine?

8
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.599
-Oh. the break room's fine.
-JAY: Ooh.

9
00:00:31.699 --> 00:00:34.234
Is that a Piaggi? I tried to get
one of those for the restaurant.

10
00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:36.771
-Those things are. like.
ten grand.
-Oh. uh.

11
00:00:36.871 --> 00:00:38.438
-we got a good deal.
-SUE: Sorry to interrupt. Chief.

12
00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:40.274
but for the Humvee.
do we want to go

13
00:00:40.374 --> 00:00:42.242
with the upgraded Napa leather
with the contrast stitching?

14
00:00:42.342 --> 00:00:43.878
JIM:
That doesn't come with

15
00:00:43.978 --> 00:00:45.445
-the premium package?
-It's separate.

16
00:00:45.547 --> 00:00:48.115
Sure. Why not? (chuckles)

17
00:00:48.215 --> 00:00:50.618
Well. that all sounds
pretty expensive.

18
00:00:50.718 --> 00:00:54.221
Ma'am. you can't put a price
on public safety.

19
00:00:54.321 --> 00:00:56.123
We're never getting
our money back. are we?

20
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:58.125
No. you are not.
But...

21
00:00:58.225 --> 00:01:00.562
I can offer you a cappuccino.

22
00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:04.933
-Okay.
-Can I get light foam?

23
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:07.100
♪ ♪

24
00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.573
<i>SAMANTHA: So. yeah.</i>

25
00:01:11.673 --> 00:01:14.141
we are facing some
financial difficulties. and

26
00:01:14.241 --> 00:01:16.644
we just thought that it was
important to come clean to you.

27
00:01:16.744 --> 00:01:19.446
Mm. "Come clean"
is a bit strong.

28
00:01:19.547 --> 00:01:21.281
The man still doesn't know

29
00:01:21.381 --> 00:01:24.351
that the root of your money woes
is ghost-related tax evasion.

30
00:01:24.451 --> 00:01:26.588
-The details are not important.
-Hmm.
-JAY: We knew we had to

31
00:01:26.688 --> 00:01:28.990
share it with you. 'cause you're
not just our business partner.

32
00:01:29.089 --> 00:01:30.424
I mean. you're our friend.

33
00:01:30.525 --> 00:01:31.826
(phone whooshes. chimes)

34
00:01:31.926 --> 00:01:33.628
Are you even listening. Mark?

35
00:01:33.728 --> 00:01:35.362
Hmm? Oh. yeah.
that all sounds great.

36
00:01:35.462 --> 00:01:38.498
We just told you we're in
serious financial trouble.

37
00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:40.167
You're right. I'm so sorry.

38
00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:41.803
Uh. they just came out
with a new update

39
00:01:41.903 --> 00:01:43.170
for this <i>Fruit Smash</i> game.

40
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:44.872
It's very addictive.

41
00:01:44.973 --> 00:01:46.808
They added raspberries.
which seems like not a big deal.

42
00:01:46.908 --> 00:01:48.843
but they give you
triple smash points.

43
00:01:48.943 --> 00:01:50.177
Look. I appreciate you guys
being honest with me.

44
00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:51.946
And I'm here
for anything you need.

45
00:01:52.046 --> 00:01:53.815
-short of lending you any money.
(laughs)
-ALBERTA: Ooh.

46
00:01:53.915 --> 00:01:56.183
-Smart man. Mark.
-We'll figure something out.

47
00:01:56.283 --> 00:01:59.520
Thank you for letting us
bend your ear. Mark.

48
00:01:59.621 --> 00:02:01.355
-Mark!
-Sorry.

49
00:02:01.455 --> 00:02:03.691
I'm just one cantaloupe away
from a fruit salad.

50
00:02:03.791 --> 00:02:05.960
-That's actually
a very big achievement.
-MARK: I'll catch

51
00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:07.361
you guys later. I'm gonna
go check out that thing

52
00:02:07.461 --> 00:02:08.663
with the walk-in
at the restaurant.

53
00:02:08.763 --> 00:02:10.865
-Thanks. Mark.
-HETTY: What...

54
00:02:10.965 --> 00:02:12.299
Now what is the plan?

55
00:02:12.399 --> 00:02:14.002
Are you gonna
have to sell the house?

56
00:02:14.102 --> 00:02:15.369
And. if so. have you considered
selling it to Kyle?

57
00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:16.838
TREVOR: Ooh! That would be

58
00:02:16.938 --> 00:02:18.205
-amazing.
-Love Kyle.

59
00:02:18.305 --> 00:02:20.140
Nobody turns a magazine page
better.

60
00:02:20.240 --> 00:02:22.209
-But. obviously.
we'd miss you dearly.
-SAMANTHA: Of course

61
00:02:22.309 --> 00:02:24.177
we don't want to sell. but
we are running out of options.

62
00:02:24.277 --> 00:02:25.647
Sam and Jay.

63
00:02:25.747 --> 00:02:28.082
-(door closes)
-Hi. Mayor Tad.

64
00:02:28.181 --> 00:02:30.183
We met last year
at that fundraiser you hosted.

65
00:02:30.283 --> 00:02:32.352
I only feel the need
to remind you because you were

66
00:02:32.452 --> 00:02:34.856
"baked out of your minds."
Your words.

67
00:02:34.956 --> 00:02:36.557
Hello. sir.

68
00:02:36.658 --> 00:02:38.860
Love a two-handed handshake.
Makes you feel special.

69
00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:41.663
Not as special
as a six-handed massage.

70
00:02:41.763 --> 00:02:43.230
Have I ever told you guys

71
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:46.067
about Jordan Belfort's
bachelor party?

72
00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:48.069
To what do we owe the pleasure.
Mr. Mayor?

73
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:50.370
Well. I know you're in a bit
of a financial pickle.

74
00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:53.173
I heard about your visit
to city hall today.

75
00:02:53.273 --> 00:02:56.010
And I think
I might have a solution.

76
00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:57.879
-We're listening.
-I would like

77
00:02:57.979 --> 00:03:00.748
to personally invest
in your business.

78
00:03:00.848 --> 00:03:02.083
The hotel. the restaurant.

79
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:03.851
I want to be part
of the solution.

80
00:03:03.951 --> 00:03:05.887
You would? But why?

81
00:03:05.987 --> 00:03:07.955
Well. obviously.
I have a special connection

82
00:03:08.056 --> 00:03:09.624
with Woodstone.

83
00:03:09.724 --> 00:03:11.291
Because your prom date
was chainsawed here. Go on.

84
00:03:11.391 --> 00:03:12.760
And you guys aren't just

85
00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:14.729
constituents.
You're job creators.

86
00:03:14.829 --> 00:03:16.564
I mean. if you were
forced to sell.

87
00:03:16.664 --> 00:03:18.265
there's no guarantee
this property wouldn't

88
00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:20.735
just become some rich person's
third house.

89
00:03:20.835 --> 00:03:22.704
I don't know if you can
technically call them rich

90
00:03:22.804 --> 00:03:24.204
if they only have three houses.
but okay.

91
00:03:24.304 --> 00:03:26.541
Well. it's definitely
interesting.

92
00:03:26.641 --> 00:03:28.576
Well. I'll tell you what.
Let's have lunch.

93
00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:31.846
talk about it.
see if this is a good fit.

94
00:03:32.847 --> 00:03:34.882
Thank you. Mr. Mayor.

95
00:03:35.850 --> 00:03:37.451
HETTY:
Mm. now. Jay's

96
00:03:37.552 --> 00:03:39.419
-double-handing it.
-This is too many hands.

97
00:03:41.321 --> 00:03:42.222
<i>SASAPPIS:</i>
<i>Thank you all</i>

98
00:03:42.322 --> 00:03:43.624
for gathering.

99
00:03:43.725 --> 00:03:45.292
The day has finally arrived.

100
00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:47.762
Ghost representative
election day.

101
00:03:47.862 --> 00:03:51.132
And now let's hear closing
statements from our candidates.

102
00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:54.902
First up. somehow representing
the basement ghosts.

103
00:03:55.002 --> 00:03:56.604
Isaac Higgintoot.

104
00:03:56.704 --> 00:03:58.438
(clears throat)
Thank you. Sasappis.

105
00:03:59.406 --> 00:04:01.142
My fellow Ghostmericans.

106
00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:03.678
it has been a long
and eventful campaign.

107
00:04:03.778 --> 00:04:05.980
And I have heard your problems.

108
00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:08.482
and I have formulated solutions.

109
00:04:08.583 --> 00:04:12.153
Remember. a vote for Isaac
is a vote

110
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:14.756
for a movie-theater style
popcorn machine

111
00:04:14.856 --> 00:04:17.424
in the main lobby.

112
00:04:17.525 --> 00:04:19.493
-Oh. yes!
-ISAAC: And this is not

113
00:04:19.594 --> 00:04:21.261
a false promise.

114
00:04:21.361 --> 00:04:23.965
I have actually secured
Samantha's agreement on this.

115
00:04:24.065 --> 00:04:27.635
The aromatic scent
of freshly popped corn

116
00:04:27.735 --> 00:04:29.302
will waft

117
00:04:29.402 --> 00:04:32.439
through these halls.
you have my word.

118
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:34.474
-Yeah!
-Whoo!

119
00:04:34.575 --> 00:04:37.344
And now. representing
the upstairs ghosts.

120
00:04:37.444 --> 00:04:39.847
Flower Montero.

121
00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:42.683
I'm nervous. I told her
she should walk through Gabe

122
00:04:42.784 --> 00:04:45.019
to get smart before her speech.
but she refused.

123
00:04:45.119 --> 00:04:46.621
Wanted to do it on her own.

124
00:04:46.721 --> 00:04:48.856
Thank you. fellow ghosts.

125
00:04:48.956 --> 00:04:51.526
I just have one question
for all of you.

126
00:04:51.626 --> 00:04:54.195
What is this for?

127
00:04:55.129 --> 00:04:57.632
It's your closing statement
for the election. Flower.

128
00:04:57.732 --> 00:05:00.367
Right.
The election.

129
00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:03.805
We got to run that son of a
bitch Nixon out of office. man.

130
00:05:03.905 --> 00:05:05.706
By attending music festivals.

131
00:05:05.807 --> 00:05:08.743
taking acid and sucking nitrous
out of balloons.

132
00:05:08.843 --> 00:05:10.578
Who's with me?

133
00:05:11.512 --> 00:05:14.148
Yeah!
(laughs)

134
00:05:14.248 --> 00:05:16.517
We want the movie theater
popcorn thing.

135
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:17.919
(chanting):
Popcorn thing!

136
00:05:18.019 --> 00:05:21.488
Popcorn thing!
Popcorn thing!

137
00:05:21.589 --> 00:05:23.558
-Our girl's in trouble.
-Popcorn thing! Pop...

138
00:05:23.658 --> 00:05:25.492
<i>TAD:</i>
<i>I got to say.</i>

139
00:05:25.593 --> 00:05:28.996
the B and B is charming as hell.
this restaurant is incredible.

140
00:05:29.096 --> 00:05:30.998
and neither of you
currently seems

141
00:05:31.098 --> 00:05:33.034
the least bit stoned.

142
00:05:33.134 --> 00:05:34.569
Ah.
The lowest of bars. cleared.

143
00:05:34.669 --> 00:05:36.170
-You love to see it.
-(chuckles)

144
00:05:36.270 --> 00:05:37.939
So. long story short--
I don't know--

145
00:05:38.039 --> 00:05:39.406
I'm feeling pretty good
about this.

146
00:05:39.507 --> 00:05:41.108
We certainly need the money.

147
00:05:41.209 --> 00:05:43.611
But cards on the table--
we're a little worried

148
00:05:43.711 --> 00:05:46.814
about selling a majority stake
in Woodstone. Right. Sam?

149
00:05:47.982 --> 00:05:50.251
-Sam?
-Oh. Sorry.

150
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:52.452
I downloaded the stupid game.
I can't put it down.

151
00:05:52.553 --> 00:05:55.189
I can help you get past that
Monster Melon. Let's talk later.

152
00:05:55.289 --> 00:05:58.726
-Now. where were we?
-Look. I completely get it.

153
00:05:58.826 --> 00:06:01.262
Woodstone isn't just a business.
It's your home.

154
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:03.764
Which you are going to lose
unless you close this deal.

155
00:06:03.865 --> 00:06:05.600
I don't know what there even is
to talk about.

156
00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:07.668
TAD:
But it's you guys
I'm investing in.

157
00:06:07.735 --> 00:06:09.402
I don't have time
to be hands-on.

158
00:06:09.503 --> 00:06:11.739
I like what you're doing.
I want you to keep doing it.

159
00:06:11.839 --> 00:06:13.440
So you're saying
you want to give us money

160
00:06:13.541 --> 00:06:14.942
to save the business
so we can keep running it.

161
00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:16.577
and nothing's gonna change?

162
00:06:16.677 --> 00:06:18.445
She's one of the great
summarizers of her era.

163
00:06:18.546 --> 00:06:20.548
Yes.
And. you know.

164
00:06:20.648 --> 00:06:22.415
if a few headlines
pop up here and there

165
00:06:22.516 --> 00:06:24.417
about how Mayor Tad
saved a local business

166
00:06:24.518 --> 00:06:27.454
in an election year.
well. you know. so be it.

167
00:06:27.555 --> 00:06:30.091
So. what do you say?

168
00:06:31.192 --> 00:06:33.194
Uh... we're in.

169
00:06:33.261 --> 00:06:34.962
Woodstone is saved!

170
00:06:35.062 --> 00:06:36.496
And it still doesn't mean
you can't ask Kyle to move in.

171
00:06:36.597 --> 00:06:38.766
Hey. Jay. bad news
on the walk-in. Looks like

172
00:06:38.866 --> 00:06:40.433
you might need
a new control board.

173
00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:43.571
Oh.
Hello. Tad.

174
00:06:43.671 --> 00:06:44.972
Mark.

175
00:06:45.072 --> 00:06:46.908
You two know each other?

176
00:06:48.441 --> 00:06:50.011
PETE:
Am I crazy or do

177
00:06:50.111 --> 00:06:51.478
Mark and Tad have
some sort of score to settle?

178
00:06:51.579 --> 00:06:52.980
TAD:
Mark did some work

179
00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:54.582
-on my kitchen.
-JAY: Great.

180
00:06:54.682 --> 00:06:55.950
He's our business partner.
(chuckles)

181
00:06:56.050 --> 00:06:57.318
He's the best.

182
00:06:57.417 --> 00:06:59.620
Tad's interested
in purchasing a part

183
00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:01.155
of our share of the business.

184
00:07:01.255 --> 00:07:03.257
I was interested.

185
00:07:03.357 --> 00:07:06.459
Unfortunately.
if Mark's involved. I'm out.

186
00:07:08.529 --> 00:07:10.197
What did Mark do
to this man's kitchen?

187
00:07:10.298 --> 00:07:12.432
I ain't leaving.
I want to find out.

188
00:07:16.737 --> 00:07:19.507
I'm sorry. Are you saying
you're not gonna invest

189
00:07:19.607 --> 00:07:21.509
in the business
because Mark is involved?

190
00:07:21.609 --> 00:07:23.778
That's right.
Going into business with someone

191
00:07:23.878 --> 00:07:25.445
is all about trust. and Mark

192
00:07:25.546 --> 00:07:27.682
is not to be trusted.

193
00:07:27.782 --> 00:07:29.650
You said you wanted
bullnose countertops.

194
00:07:29.717 --> 00:07:31.018
I would never.

195
00:07:31.118 --> 00:07:33.453
Everything about me
says sharp edges.

196
00:07:33.554 --> 00:07:35.856
Guys. this doesn't
need to be a big deal.

197
00:07:35.957 --> 00:07:37.858
-Misunderstandings happen.
-TAD: Yeah.

198
00:07:37.959 --> 00:07:39.660
It wasn't a misunderstanding.
I couldn't have been clearer.

199
00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:41.696
Yeah. I agree.

200
00:07:41.796 --> 00:07:43.197
When we discussed this.
standing in your kitchen.

201
00:07:43.297 --> 00:07:46.167
you clearly stated
you wanted bullnose.

202
00:07:48.135 --> 00:07:49.503
That is not what I said.

203
00:07:49.603 --> 00:07:51.238
Two alphas going at it.
I'm loving it.

204
00:07:51.339 --> 00:07:53.473
Yup.
She loves alphas.

205
00:07:53.574 --> 00:07:56.377
Look. I like you guys.
I like your business.

206
00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:59.880
I like the optics
of me saving the day.

207
00:07:59.981 --> 00:08:01.315
But it's either him or me.

208
00:08:01.415 --> 00:08:02.850
Let me know what you decide.

209
00:08:04.685 --> 00:08:06.320
Screw that guy.

210
00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:09.824
Trust me.
you're better off without him.

211
00:08:09.924 --> 00:08:11.859
Oy vey.
That deal fell apart faster

212
00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:15.495
than when I took the Hobby Lobby
guys to Scores for lap dances.

213
00:08:15.596 --> 00:08:18.032
What are we supposed to do?
We're deep in debt.

214
00:08:18.132 --> 00:08:19.900
We need this Tad deal
to go through. babe.

215
00:08:20.001 --> 00:08:21.235
You got to solve
the Tad-Mark beef.

216
00:08:21.335 --> 00:08:23.104
Get those two
to kiss and make up.

217
00:08:23.204 --> 00:08:24.872
Alberta says we need to get Tad
and Mark to resolve their issue.

218
00:08:24.972 --> 00:08:27.341
How?
It's a he said-he said.

219
00:08:27.441 --> 00:08:30.044
No one who wasn't standing
in that kitchen with them

220
00:08:30.144 --> 00:08:32.580
knows the truth
about how it really went down.

221
00:08:32.680 --> 00:08:34.582
Then why don't we see if
anyone else was in that kitchen?

222
00:08:34.682 --> 00:08:36.183
HETTY:
You've got ghosts.

223
00:08:36.283 --> 00:08:38.052
Specifically. one who can
leave the property.

224
00:08:38.152 --> 00:08:41.255
Okay. Jay. what if we sent Pete
over to Tad's house

225
00:08:41.355 --> 00:08:43.457
to see if there were any ghosts
who witnessed the conversation

226
00:08:43.557 --> 00:08:45.259
that Mark and Tad
are arguing about?

227
00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:47.862
Maybe there's a ghost
who heard something helpful.

228
00:08:47.962 --> 00:08:49.630
Interesting.
It's worth a shot.

229
00:08:49.730 --> 00:08:51.432
HETTY:
And if it doesn't work out.

230
00:08:51.532 --> 00:08:53.234
are debtors' prisons
still a thing?

231
00:08:53.334 --> 00:08:55.770
They may be satisfied
with just the husband.

232
00:08:55.870 --> 00:08:57.772
That's some good news.

233
00:08:57.872 --> 00:08:59.907
<i>NANCY:</i>
<i>I cast my vote for...</i>

234
00:09:00.007 --> 00:09:02.743
-Isaac.
-(laughs) Thank you.

235
00:09:02.843 --> 00:09:04.445
Another mark
in the Higgintoot column.

236
00:09:04.545 --> 00:09:06.914
This is turning into
a bit of a landslide.

237
00:09:07.014 --> 00:09:08.616
Don't be down. Flower.

238
00:09:08.716 --> 00:09:12.086
There is still time
to turn this ship around.

239
00:09:12.186 --> 00:09:14.889
Is boat analogy 'cause. Viking.

240
00:09:14.989 --> 00:09:16.791
You're the best. Thor.

241
00:09:16.891 --> 00:09:18.959
I would like to vote in the
ghost representative election.

242
00:09:19.060 --> 00:09:21.929
Though I prefer theocracy
over democracy.

243
00:09:22.029 --> 00:09:24.632
Hi. Patience.
It's been a minute.

244
00:09:24.732 --> 00:09:27.601
Haven't seen you since the whole
Christmas canoodle with Trevor.

245
00:09:27.701 --> 00:09:29.637
A lapse we shall not
speak of again.

246
00:09:29.737 --> 00:09:32.573
He proved
to be a man of low morals.

247
00:09:32.673 --> 00:09:35.810
his thick thighs and sublime
buttocks notwithstanding.

248
00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:38.412
Which leads me to the only
question that matters.

249
00:09:38.513 --> 00:09:39.980
For whom did Trevor vote?

250
00:09:40.081 --> 00:09:41.982
He voted for Isaac.

251
00:09:42.083 --> 00:09:44.452
Ah. Then I shall cast my vote
for Flower.

252
00:09:44.553 --> 00:09:47.254
-Oh. right on.
-ISAAC (laughing): No matter.

253
00:09:47.354 --> 00:09:48.856
My lead is still comfortable.

254
00:09:48.956 --> 00:09:50.491
RICHARD:
Not so fast.

255
00:09:50.591 --> 00:09:52.626
The bunker ghosts
cast their votes for Flower.

256
00:09:52.726 --> 00:09:53.928
(laughing):
Oh. hey. guys.

257
00:09:54.028 --> 00:09:56.931
ISAAC:
What? My former brethren.

258
00:09:57.031 --> 00:10:00.000
Did our four hours in the cult
together mean nothing?

259
00:10:00.101 --> 00:10:02.002
Oh. sorry. Isaac.

260
00:10:02.103 --> 00:10:04.939
but Flower freed us
from Bruce's evil clutches.

261
00:10:05.039 --> 00:10:07.475
And by my count. that is...

262
00:10:07.576 --> 00:10:09.176
seven more votes for Flower.

263
00:10:09.276 --> 00:10:12.113
And we're tied. folks.

264
00:10:12.213 --> 00:10:13.781
-(laughs boisterously)
-ISAAC: No. no.

265
00:10:13.881 --> 00:10:15.483
FLOWER:
Isaac. it's kind of a bummer

266
00:10:15.584 --> 00:10:17.351
for either of us
to have to lose.

267
00:10:17.451 --> 00:10:20.522
What if we just did the ghost
representative thing together?

268
00:10:20.621 --> 00:10:22.690
A power-sharing arrangement?

269
00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:24.959
Never.
I have an idea.

270
00:10:26.927 --> 00:10:29.029
So. you guys all still just

271
00:10:29.130 --> 00:10:30.965
staying in bunker?

272
00:10:31.065 --> 00:10:32.366
Yeah. Just seemed
like the easiest thing.

273
00:10:32.466 --> 00:10:33.968
Plus. the cots are super nice

274
00:10:34.068 --> 00:10:36.036
now that the coroner
removed all our corpses.

275
00:10:36.137 --> 00:10:37.872
Yeah. it's a total refresh.

276
00:10:37.972 --> 00:10:39.541
-Hmm.
-Oh.

277
00:10:39.640 --> 00:10:41.208
PETE:
Well.

278
00:10:41.308 --> 00:10:44.078
turns out a ghost
at the mayor's house did witness

279
00:10:44.178 --> 00:10:46.515
the infamous bullnose counter
discussion in question.

280
00:10:46.615 --> 00:10:48.349
Really?

281
00:10:48.449 --> 00:10:51.018
Pete says a ghost at Tad's place
did witness the conversation.

282
00:10:51.118 --> 00:10:53.721
And the verdict is...
(imitates drumroll)

283
00:10:53.821 --> 00:10:55.222
Tad was telling the truth.

284
00:10:55.322 --> 00:10:57.892
-(gasps) Mark is lying?
-Seriously?

285
00:10:57.992 --> 00:10:59.693
Not lying.
Mistaken.

286
00:10:59.793 --> 00:11:01.762
Uh. apparently. the original
agreement had been

287
00:11:01.862 --> 00:11:03.397
to install
the bullnose countertops.

288
00:11:03.497 --> 00:11:05.199
Mark had sold the mayor
on the idea

289
00:11:05.299 --> 00:11:06.734
that they were
a "classic aesthetic

290
00:11:06.834 --> 00:11:08.503
that would stand
the test of time."

291
00:11:08.603 --> 00:11:10.704
Same reason I installed
an aquarium wall in my condo.

292
00:11:10.804 --> 00:11:12.206
PETE:
But importantly.

293
00:11:12.306 --> 00:11:14.074
this conversation happened
two years ago.

294
00:11:14.175 --> 00:11:17.178
coinciding exactly
with the last major update

295
00:11:17.278 --> 00:11:19.046
to the game <i>Fruit Smash.</i>

296
00:11:20.014 --> 00:11:21.415
Okay.

297
00:11:21.516 --> 00:11:23.585
So. it turns out
the mayor was clear

298
00:11:23.684 --> 00:11:25.554
about wanting
the straight-edge countertops

299
00:11:25.654 --> 00:11:27.087
but Mark wasn't listening

300
00:11:27.188 --> 00:11:28.590
because he was busy
playing <i>Fruit Smash.</i>

301
00:11:28.689 --> 00:11:31.593
Hey. so good news
about the walk-in.

302
00:11:31.692 --> 00:11:33.260
The control board's
actually still under warranty.

303
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:34.862
so looks like
you saved a few bucks.

304
00:11:34.962 --> 00:11:36.864
Hey. Mark. the whole thing

305
00:11:36.964 --> 00:11:38.265
that happened
with the mayor's kitchen--

306
00:11:38.365 --> 00:11:39.934
when was that. exactly?

307
00:11:40.034 --> 00:11:42.770
Hmm. it's got to be...
couple years ago. now.

308
00:11:42.870 --> 00:11:44.438
Couple years ago. Wasn't that
right around the time

309
00:11:44.539 --> 00:11:46.273
of a new <i>Fruit Smash</i> update?

310
00:11:46.373 --> 00:11:48.275
Why are you asking?

311
00:11:48.375 --> 00:11:51.613
Oh. he's thinking maybe this'll
jog Mark's memory. That's smart.

312
00:11:51.712 --> 00:11:53.747
Well. it's just. um.

313
00:11:53.847 --> 00:11:55.650
couldn't it be possible

314
00:11:55.749 --> 00:11:58.452
that the mayor was clear
about the countertops.

315
00:11:58.553 --> 00:12:00.421
and you weren't listening

316
00:12:00.522 --> 00:12:02.624
because you were smashing fruit?

317
00:12:02.723 --> 00:12:05.125
(scoffs)
I see what's going on here.

318
00:12:05.226 --> 00:12:07.061
Look. if you want
to side with the rich guy

319
00:12:07.161 --> 00:12:09.797
so you can get
your precious money. go for it.

320
00:12:09.897 --> 00:12:11.966
No. Mark.
It's not like that.

321
00:12:12.066 --> 00:12:13.635
I'm your friend
and your partner.

322
00:12:13.734 --> 00:12:15.436
If you should believe anybody.

323
00:12:15.537 --> 00:12:16.804
it's me.
'cause I'm in the right here.

324
00:12:16.904 --> 00:12:18.973
Of course you are.

325
00:12:19.073 --> 00:12:20.542
But what if you're not?

326
00:12:22.544 --> 00:12:24.411
You know what?
Forget you guys.

327
00:12:24.512 --> 00:12:27.582
You want to get into bed
with Tad? Go for it.

328
00:12:27.682 --> 00:12:28.983
But make sure
he buys my share. too.

329
00:12:29.083 --> 00:12:30.317
'cause I don't want
to be in business

330
00:12:30.417 --> 00:12:31.653
with people
who don't even trust me.

331
00:12:31.785 --> 00:12:32.853
Mark. wait.

332
00:12:35.523 --> 00:12:37.958
How do you get past
Commander Cantaloupe?

333
00:12:42.597 --> 00:12:44.265
<i>JAY:</i>
<i>Great. My best friend hates me</i>

334
00:12:44.365 --> 00:12:45.299
and thinks I don't trust him.

335
00:12:45.366 --> 00:12:46.867
Whoa. best friend?

336
00:12:46.967 --> 00:12:49.169
He means best visible friend.
baby. He's upset.

337
00:12:49.270 --> 00:12:51.972
Yes. this is unfortunate

338
00:12:52.072 --> 00:12:53.340
on a personal level.

339
00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:54.942
But at the end of the day.
with Mark

340
00:12:55.042 --> 00:12:56.477
hating you
and wanting to be bought out.

341
00:12:56.578 --> 00:12:58.979
the path is cleared
for a deal with Tad.

342
00:12:59.079 --> 00:13:00.515
Hetty's saying
that with Mark walking.

343
00:13:00.615 --> 00:13:02.783
it does kind of solve
our problem with Tad.

344
00:13:02.883 --> 00:13:04.485
I don't want
to solve our problem this way.

345
00:13:04.586 --> 00:13:06.253
There wouldn't be a restaurant
if it wasn't for Mark.

346
00:13:06.353 --> 00:13:08.322
I know.
It doesn't feel good.

347
00:13:08.422 --> 00:13:10.324
-Again. it was Hetty.
-Mm.

348
00:13:10.424 --> 00:13:11.859
-This is a stressful situation.
-TREVOR: Yeah.

349
00:13:11.959 --> 00:13:13.327
these kids could both benefit

350
00:13:13.427 --> 00:13:15.329
from a little
six-handed massage action.

351
00:13:15.429 --> 00:13:17.498
I know these chicks
from the Belfort bach.

352
00:13:17.599 --> 00:13:19.133
They're probably
in their 60s now.

353
00:13:19.233 --> 00:13:21.201
but if you close your eyes.
their hands are 25.

354
00:13:21.302 --> 00:13:23.203
JAY:
You know what?
Mark doesn't think

355
00:13:23.304 --> 00:13:25.339
that we trust him.
but I know a way

356
00:13:25.439 --> 00:13:27.207
that we can prove to him
that we do.

357
00:13:27.308 --> 00:13:28.976
Come with me. Sam.

358
00:13:31.145 --> 00:13:33.013
Six-handed massage.

359
00:13:33.113 --> 00:13:34.716
You are classless.

360
00:13:34.815 --> 00:13:36.984
My aquarium wall would disagree.

361
00:13:38.787 --> 00:13:40.020
<i>SASAPPIS:</i>
<i>Okay. well.</i>

362
00:13:40.120 --> 00:13:41.723
with all the votes recorded.

363
00:13:41.822 --> 00:13:44.726
it's looking like
this is an unprecedented tie.

364
00:13:44.825 --> 00:13:47.061
-(lively chatter)
-Unless there's

365
00:13:47.161 --> 00:13:48.563
anybody who hasn't voted yet.

366
00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:51.165
In fact. there is someone

367
00:13:51.265 --> 00:13:52.600
who hasn't voted yet.

368
00:13:53.668 --> 00:13:55.737
Bruce. the time has arrived.

369
00:13:55.836 --> 00:13:58.038
-(lively chatter)
-Oh. my God.

370
00:13:58.138 --> 00:13:59.708
Howdy. everyone.

371
00:13:59.808 --> 00:14:00.742
Oh. boy.

372
00:14:00.841 --> 00:14:02.109
Where he come from?

373
00:14:02.209 --> 00:14:03.745
We summoned him from the dirt.

374
00:14:03.844 --> 00:14:05.412
We played Cream
over a loudspeaker

375
00:14:05.513 --> 00:14:07.749
until he came
through the basement wall.

376
00:14:07.848 --> 00:14:09.350
Sorry. Flower.

377
00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:12.219
Really want to smell
that movie-theater butter.

378
00:14:12.319 --> 00:14:14.254
SASAPPIS:
Um. okay. so. uh.

379
00:14:14.355 --> 00:14:16.691
probably a formality. but Bruce.

380
00:14:16.791 --> 00:14:19.093
who do you vote for?

381
00:14:19.193 --> 00:14:22.429
Who do I vote for?
Hmm.

382
00:14:22.530 --> 00:14:24.699
That is a very
interesting question.

383
00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:27.901
I spent the last month

384
00:14:28.001 --> 00:14:30.705
wandering around
in a dark exile.

385
00:14:30.805 --> 00:14:32.439
foisted upon me

386
00:14:32.540 --> 00:14:35.577
by this traitorous woman
I now stand before.

387
00:14:35.677 --> 00:14:37.612
Not looking good for Flower.

388
00:14:37.712 --> 00:14:40.114
I had a lot of time
to think in the dirt.

389
00:14:40.214 --> 00:14:43.785
Think about ways
to plot revenge.

390
00:14:43.884 --> 00:14:46.755
-Ah.
-But then
a funny thing happened.

391
00:14:46.855 --> 00:14:49.390
Between the bouts of pure panic.

392
00:14:49.490 --> 00:14:52.092
there was a clarity
that settled in.

393
00:14:52.192 --> 00:14:54.128
And I realized

394
00:14:54.228 --> 00:14:55.864
I was grateful to Flower.

395
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:58.633
-I'm sorry. What?
-ALBERTA: Oh.

396
00:14:58.733 --> 00:15:01.803
-this is taking a turn.
-For. by exposing me

397
00:15:01.902 --> 00:15:03.237
as a fraud.

398
00:15:03.337 --> 00:15:05.573
she freed me
from my web of lies.

399
00:15:05.673 --> 00:15:07.441
It is for that reason

400
00:15:07.542 --> 00:15:10.310
that I cast my deciding vote...

401
00:15:10.411 --> 00:15:12.814
-for Sister Flower.
-(all exclaim)

402
00:15:12.913 --> 00:15:14.314
Oh. come on.

403
00:15:14.415 --> 00:15:16.316
Then it's official.
Flower is the winner.

404
00:15:16.417 --> 00:15:18.419
We have a new
Ghost Representative.

405
00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:20.555
-FLOWER: Yay!
-ALBERTA: Yeah. Flower. Yeah!
-(applause)

406
00:15:21.556 --> 00:15:22.990
Hey. Mark. wait.

407
00:15:23.090 --> 00:15:24.659
There's nothing left
to talk about. Jay.

408
00:15:24.759 --> 00:15:26.360
You have every reason
to be mad at us.

409
00:15:26.460 --> 00:15:28.162
We accused you of something
that we couldn't prove.

410
00:15:28.262 --> 00:15:29.997
But here's the thing. We don't
just think you were wrong.

411
00:15:30.097 --> 00:15:31.833
We know you were wrong.

412
00:15:31.932 --> 00:15:33.835
-I'm sorry. is this an apology?
-SAMANTHA: The reason that

413
00:15:33.934 --> 00:15:35.469
we know what happened
in that mayor's kitchen...

414
00:15:37.204 --> 00:15:39.774
...is a ghost told us.

415
00:15:39.874 --> 00:15:41.008
What?

416
00:15:41.108 --> 00:15:42.677
Sam can see ghosts.

417
00:15:42.777 --> 00:15:44.512
And we have a ghost
on our property

418
00:15:44.612 --> 00:15:45.946
who can travel
to other properties.

419
00:15:46.046 --> 00:15:48.015
It's a very rare
and cool ghost power.

420
00:15:48.115 --> 00:15:50.618
Anyway. our ghost talked
to a ghost at Tad's house.

421
00:15:50.718 --> 00:15:52.219
and that's how
we know what happened.

422
00:15:52.319 --> 00:15:53.855
-This is insane.
-SAMANTHA: This is us

423
00:15:53.954 --> 00:15:55.824
showing you
how much we trust you.

424
00:15:55.924 --> 00:15:58.025
By letting you in on
our most closely-guarded secret.

425
00:15:58.125 --> 00:16:00.194
Sam. ask the ghosts
to do that thing where

426
00:16:00.294 --> 00:16:01.663
they prove their existence.
You're gonna love this.

427
00:16:01.763 --> 00:16:03.096
SAMANTHA:
Uh. sweetie. there aren't

428
00:16:03.197 --> 00:16:04.833
-any ghosts out here.
-Seriously?

429
00:16:04.933 --> 00:16:06.868
They're always around
except when you need 'em.

430
00:16:06.967 --> 00:16:09.303
I'm gonna go.
Don't call me.

431
00:16:09.403 --> 00:16:10.872
Mark. hold on!

432
00:16:10.971 --> 00:16:13.373
Just come back in the house.
We'll find a ghost

433
00:16:13.474 --> 00:16:15.577
and then. we'll
straighten this all out.

434
00:16:15.677 --> 00:16:17.144
Please.

435
00:16:17.244 --> 00:16:20.347
Mark. you are
my best visible friend.

436
00:16:20.447 --> 00:16:23.016
I promise you.
I wouldn't make this up.

437
00:16:24.652 --> 00:16:26.153
Prove it.

438
00:16:27.154 --> 00:16:28.322
SAMANTHA:
You know what. I think
they're in the barn.

439
00:16:28.422 --> 00:16:29.524
Follow me.

440
00:16:29.624 --> 00:16:32.059
Yep. here are the ghosts.

441
00:16:32.159 --> 00:16:33.695
They're gathered
for the ghost election.

442
00:16:33.761 --> 00:16:35.262
Right.
The ghost election.

443
00:16:35.362 --> 00:16:38.566
Samantha. I have suffered
an ignominious defeat.

444
00:16:38.666 --> 00:16:41.536
but I would like to request
that you still go forward

445
00:16:41.636 --> 00:16:43.571
with installing the
movie-theater popcorn machine

446
00:16:43.671 --> 00:16:46.908
in the lobby.
because the people deserve it.

447
00:16:47.007 --> 00:16:48.576
-Aw.
-Oh. hey.

448
00:16:48.676 --> 00:16:50.210
What are you talking about?

449
00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:52.714
What movie-theater
popcorn machine?

450
00:16:52.814 --> 00:16:54.248
I asked you earlier.

451
00:16:54.348 --> 00:16:55.750
We had a whole conversation.

452
00:16:55.850 --> 00:16:58.753
Was I playing a game
on my phone?

453
00:16:58.853 --> 00:17:00.087
-Perhaps.
-Yeah. I don't

454
00:17:00.187 --> 00:17:01.623
remember agreeing
to any of that.

455
00:17:01.723 --> 00:17:03.390
And it sounds insane

456
00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:04.859
and expensive. so. sorry.

457
00:17:04.959 --> 00:17:07.762
Oh. A colonial ghost
wants a popcorn machine.

458
00:17:07.862 --> 00:17:09.229
Welcome to my life.

459
00:17:09.329 --> 00:17:10.899
(laughs)
Guys. listen up.

460
00:17:10.999 --> 00:17:12.934
We told Mark that Sam
can talk to ghosts. and we

461
00:17:13.033 --> 00:17:14.769
need your help proving it.
so. uh. check his pockets.

462
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.771
see how many fingers
he's got behind his back.

463
00:17:16.871 --> 00:17:18.773
You know. the classics.

464
00:17:18.873 --> 00:17:21.441
We happy to help.
Want Thor do light thing?

465
00:17:21.543 --> 00:17:24.478
Yes. great. The Viking ghost
is gonna make the lights blink.

466
00:17:24.579 --> 00:17:26.648
-Ah.
-Yeah.

467
00:17:27.749 --> 00:17:29.651
Wait one second. Thor.

468
00:17:30.718 --> 00:17:32.554
I hate to do this.

469
00:17:32.654 --> 00:17:34.454
but I do have
a fiduciary responsibility

470
00:17:34.556 --> 00:17:35.957
to my constituents.

471
00:17:36.056 --> 00:17:37.792
We'll prove your abilities
to Mark.

472
00:17:37.892 --> 00:17:39.727
but we need your word
that you will procure

473
00:17:39.827 --> 00:17:41.963
that popcorn machine
for the lobby.

474
00:17:42.062 --> 00:17:43.263
Damn. Flower.
Did you walk through Gabe?

475
00:17:43.363 --> 00:17:45.967
No.
I'm just momentarily lucid.

476
00:17:46.066 --> 00:17:48.302
So. what's supposed
to happen here?

477
00:17:48.402 --> 00:17:50.572
Uh. Flower.
are you extorting us?

478
00:17:50.672 --> 00:17:52.139
Oh. yeah.
Big time.

479
00:17:52.239 --> 00:17:53.975
My God.

480
00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:56.143
-She's good at this.
-SAMANTHA: Okay.

481
00:17:56.243 --> 00:17:58.145
Fine. You can have
the popcorn machine.

482
00:17:58.245 --> 00:18:00.648
-Yeah!
-(cheering. laughing)

483
00:18:00.748 --> 00:18:02.784
Thorfinn. do your thing.

484
00:18:02.884 --> 00:18:04.284
Ah.

485
00:18:04.384 --> 00:18:06.253
-(shouts)
-(lights buzzing)

486
00:18:08.121 --> 00:18:09.991
And that's just an amuse-bouche.

487
00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:12.026
There's more.

488
00:18:14.094 --> 00:18:15.697
On the one hand.
I can't believe it.

489
00:18:15.797 --> 00:18:18.332
But on the other hand.
it explains so much.

490
00:18:18.432 --> 00:18:20.334
I mean. no offense. Sam. but

491
00:18:20.434 --> 00:18:22.837
your behavior has been
deeply weird for years.

492
00:18:22.937 --> 00:18:24.872
A lot of that behavior
has nothing to do with ghosts.

493
00:18:24.973 --> 00:18:27.374
We probably should have
told you a lot sooner.

494
00:18:27.474 --> 00:18:29.176
We've told very few people.

495
00:18:29.276 --> 00:18:31.311
Oh. My office said
you wanted to speak.

496
00:18:31.411 --> 00:18:32.947
No.
What is he doing here?

497
00:18:33.047 --> 00:18:35.415
Did I not make myself clear?
If he's in. I'm out.

498
00:18:35.516 --> 00:18:37.619
I asked Sam and Jay
to get in touch with you.

499
00:18:37.719 --> 00:18:39.554
There's something I want to say.

500
00:18:39.654 --> 00:18:41.488
Please just hear him out. Tad.

501
00:18:41.589 --> 00:18:44.692
After replaying things
in my mind a little bit.

502
00:18:44.792 --> 00:18:47.962
I think. uh.
maybe I got it wrong.

503
00:18:48.062 --> 00:18:50.531
-Really?
-I know I got it wrong.

504
00:18:50.632 --> 00:18:54.201
So. I'm sorry.
And as a gesture of my remorse.

505
00:18:54.301 --> 00:18:57.105
I'm willing to redo
the countertops. free of charge.

506
00:18:59.641 --> 00:19:01.475
Actually. the bullnose
kind of grew on me.

507
00:19:01.576 --> 00:19:04.211
-Seriously?
-TAD: You were right. man.
It's timeless.

508
00:19:04.311 --> 00:19:05.580
It was just the principle
of the thing.

509
00:19:05.680 --> 00:19:07.548
Your apology--

510
00:19:07.649 --> 00:19:08.783
that's good enough for me.

511
00:19:08.883 --> 00:19:10.718
So we have a deal?

512
00:19:10.818 --> 00:19:12.219
We have a deal.

513
00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:13.420
(laughing)

514
00:19:13.521 --> 00:19:15.690
Woodstone is saved!

515
00:19:15.757 --> 00:19:17.091
I know I screamed that earlier.

516
00:19:17.190 --> 00:19:18.760
but this time.
I think it's gonna stick.

517
00:19:23.631 --> 00:19:25.700
Oh.
Hey. man.

518
00:19:25.800 --> 00:19:27.902
Madame Representative.

519
00:19:28.002 --> 00:19:30.404
Isaac. we're friends.

520
00:19:30.505 --> 00:19:32.239
You can call me Jennifer.

521
00:19:32.339 --> 00:19:33.841
Wait. that doesn't sound right.

522
00:19:33.941 --> 00:19:36.077
Did you come here
to gloat. Flower?

523
00:19:36.176 --> 00:19:38.079
Is this the type of reception
I have to look forward to

524
00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:39.580
over the next four years?

525
00:19:39.681 --> 00:19:43.084
No. I actually came
to ask you for help.

526
00:19:43.183 --> 00:19:45.586
It's just. ghost rep
seems like such a big job.

527
00:19:45.687 --> 00:19:48.589
And I don't really have a lot
of experience with politics.

528
00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:51.759
I mean. I was orgy co-chair
of my cult.

529
00:19:51.859 --> 00:19:53.928
but that was mostly
just picking the music.

530
00:19:54.028 --> 00:19:56.731
What I'm saying is...

531
00:19:57.464 --> 00:20:00.367
...I think I might
need a vice ghost rep.

532
00:20:01.368 --> 00:20:03.370
Really?

533
00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:05.039
It's just. I don't really
have the time.

534
00:20:05.139 --> 00:20:06.808
I could use help
carrying the load.

535
00:20:06.908 --> 00:20:09.644
You know. public appearances.
glad-handing.

536
00:20:09.744 --> 00:20:11.244
All the boring stuff

537
00:20:11.344 --> 00:20:13.815
where people are really just
kissing your butt.

538
00:20:13.915 --> 00:20:15.950
I mean...

539
00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:17.484
I mean. I suppose.
if it would help you.

540
00:20:17.585 --> 00:20:19.319
I could...

541
00:20:19.419 --> 00:20:21.589
take some of that butt-kiss
receiving off of your plate.

542
00:20:21.689 --> 00:20:24.759
Mm. I really
appreciate this. Isaac.

543
00:20:24.859 --> 00:20:26.060
You're welcome. Flower.

544
00:20:26.160 --> 00:20:28.261
And if you must know.

545
00:20:28.328 --> 00:20:29.664
I actually think

546
00:20:29.764 --> 00:20:31.431
you're not going to be
terrible at this.

547
00:20:31.532 --> 00:20:32.800
With my help. of course.

548
00:20:32.900 --> 00:20:34.468
Not terrible at what?

549
00:20:34.569 --> 00:20:36.904
At being ghost representative.

550
00:20:37.004 --> 00:20:38.472
Is it hard?

551
00:20:38.573 --> 00:20:40.440
Oh. I was orgy co-chair
of my cult.

552
00:20:40.541 --> 00:20:42.944
but that was mostly
just picking the music.

553
00:20:43.044 --> 00:20:45.513
-Cool.
-Mm.
